It is important for customers to have planned sprints with start and end date before start them.
{quote}
What I would like in the end is to pre-plan more than one sprint in time and not have to necessarily have the future sprints be active.
{quote}

Unable to close Sprint with closed parent and sub-tasks issues on different workflows or statuses.
h3. Summary

Sprints that have parent issues and sub-tasks on different workflows cannot be closed and a generic error is thrown.
h3. Steps to reproduce
 # Associate the sub-task on a different workflow than the parent issue type;
 # Create a board that exclude the sub-tasks from it;
{code:java}
project = TEST AND issuetype not in subTaskIssueTypes(){code}

 # Create a sprint with one parent and one sub-task;
 # Close both issues, both must have different final statuses;
 # Try to close the sprint.

h3. Expected results

The sprint is closed since all issues on that sprint are in a closed state.
h3. Actual result

Jira throws the error "Sprint cannot be completed as there are incomplete subtasks on the following issues" instead.
 !Screen Shot 2020-04-27 at 15.17.18.png|thumbnail!
h3. Workaround

Edit the board filter to show the sub-tasks and map the sub-task status to the last column, then close the sprint.
